Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.59,0:00:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's good enough"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.66,0:00:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's good enough"?\NWhat do you mean, Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.00,0:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm calling off the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.84,0:00:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second. I'm through\Ninvestigating Karl Neumann.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.51,0:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He really is your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.48,0:00:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No, hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.08,0:00:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everything's been solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.82,0:00:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There still is a possibility that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.19,0:00:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund Fahren, the boy\Nwho pretended to be your son,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.12,0:00:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't commit suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.53,0:00:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't clear who was pulling\Nthe strings behind Fahren!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.46,0:00:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's been solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.64,0:00:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've poured some tea, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.61,0:00:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.31,0:01:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like some?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.38,0:01:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work. Send me the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.29,0:01:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather sure is nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.29,0:01:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.63,0:01:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan's coming as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.13,0:01:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. So Johan's coming along.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.30,0:01:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was a cold man.\NReserved and untrusting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.88,0:01:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who would have thought that\Nhe would transform into{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}such a good-natured old man\Nas soon as he found his son...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.62,0:01:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That smile...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I would never guess that people\Ncall him the "Vampire of Bavaria."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.49,0:01:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ah. So Johan's coming along."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.36,0:03:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're looking for this puppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.70,0:03:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.83,0:03:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that\Nmy client's ex-husband took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.54,0:03:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Even custody disputes over puppies\Ncan get messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.54,0:03:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.81,0:03:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'm going to\Nhave some wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go right ahead.\NWater is good enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.92,0:04:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Your work is slow, but you don't\Nseem interested in alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.86,0:04:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm all right in that account.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.73,0:04:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That account? Is there\Nsomething else bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.57,0:04:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have some free time\Nso I do trivial things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.20,0:04:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I look at my personal scrapbook
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.31,0:04:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of unsolved crimes from my time\Nas a police detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.38,0:04:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.18,0:04:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do you feel\Nwhen you look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.48,0:04:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This murder, that murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.89,0:04:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think that the culprits\Nare still at large...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.16,0:04:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't see them through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Not with my incompetence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.07,0:04:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the skills.\NBut you get too desperate, Richard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.20,0:04:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You get too involved in your cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.44,0:04:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You were annoyed that you couldn't\Nread the criminals' minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you got frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.25,0:04:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So I turned to alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.21,0:04:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.18,0:05:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's time to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that there's\Nanything wrong with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking through your scrapbook\Nof old cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.80,0:05:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I just become annoyed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.47,0:05:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.14,0:05:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to tell me what you think of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.94,0:05:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look through them\Nfrom your current point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You were drunk and shot down\Nthat young serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.58,0:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're ready to face that truth\Nhead on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're still running away from\Nthe thoughts you had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when you pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You still see that boy's ghost,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.74,0:05:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When everything clears up\Nand is brought to light,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that ghost will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.75,0:06:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"When everything is\Nbrought to light"' huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The "accountant murder case".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.69,0:06:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim, Joachim Holmer,\Nhad a steady career.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.16,0:06:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't the kind of person\Nwho would make enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He was stabbed to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.13,0:06:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no indication\Nthat he was robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.84,0:07:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Voice of God murder case".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.31,0:07:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims were a former\Nhousekeeper and a chauffeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.84,0:07:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The message, "I heard the voice of\NGod"' was left at both crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Dornach Company president\Nmurder case".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lute Gauk was one of\Nthe wealthiest men in Bavaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.22,0:07:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,His body was found\Nin Hartholz Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.06,0:07:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Spira couple murder case"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.57,0:07:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Spiras' drowned bodies\Nwashed up upstream
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,along the Isar River.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.20,0:07:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It is being investigated\Nas one of a series
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of middle-aged couple murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The material witness,\Na Japanese doctor, is still on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh man...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The more unsolved cases I had,\Nthe more alcohol I drank.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.92,0:07:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's different now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.26,0:08:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. It's as the doctor said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.96,0:08:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what it means\Nto think while sober...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Think hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.04,0:08:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Think hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.14,0:08:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.18,0:08:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you figure out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.41,0:08:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...about that.\NI thought of something, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:08:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw that boy's ghost\Nand you lost your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Your thoughts will\Ncome back to you sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.44,0:09:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I realize?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.64,0:09:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an important key\Nto solving one of those cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.19,0:09:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that just my imagination?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.57,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's following me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the same as before.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Back then, I was running after him\Nthrough an alley just like this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for coming\Nso late at night, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you finally feel like\Ntelling me everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.24,0:10:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.78,0:10:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I saw something\Nwithin that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.41,0:10:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I knew it existed\Nin this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.92,0:10:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,True evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I. ..I shot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! I'm glad you told me.\NYou've finally recovered!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still more.. .I realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.14,0:10:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea that popped in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.14,0:11:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The unsolved cases I had been\Nworking on were actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...a single case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.32,0:11:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dear Dr. Gillen...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The other day I read the book\Nthat you sent me,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.13,0:11:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"An introduction to Transcendental\NCriminal Psychology."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.13,0:11:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your book was\Na very interesting read.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.93,0:11:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It pleases me to see that a student\Nof mine from Düsseldorf University{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.77,0:11:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is now a leading authority\Nin the field of criminal psychology.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.94,0:11:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That aside, regarding the interview\Nyou conducted with{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the serial murderer Peter Jurgens.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You told me that Jurgens claimed that\Na friend told him to murder his victims.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.99,0:11:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My memory isn't clear,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.30,0:12:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so could you tell me again\Nthe name of Jurgens' alleged friend?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.61,0:12:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}PS.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.38,0:12:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You were a very good student\Nin college,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but there was a student in your class\Nwho was just as brilliant{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and always fought you\Nto be top of the class.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He moved on to become\Na neurosurgeon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At any rate, it seems that\Nhe's become a material witness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.06,0:12:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in a multiple homicide case.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want you to tell me anything\Nyou know about him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.97,0:12:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What kind of person is he,\Nand where might he be right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This Dr. Tenma...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.21,0:12:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it isn't that detective\Nfrom before!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm just a private detective\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.69,0:12:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for bringing up\Na painful subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:12:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but may I question you once more\Nabout the "Voice of God case"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.63,0:13:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.13,0:13:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been four years\Nand the police aren't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,putting any more energy\Ninto the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.37,0:13:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.84,0:13:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I believe your mother was once\Na housekeeper for the tycoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.25,0:13:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.08,0:13:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was already\Ntwenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.88,0:13:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did she quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.52,0:13:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She became ill at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, she only took jobs\Nclose to home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.93,0:13:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that she was\Nhaving problems with Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.26,0:13:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all!\NMy mother loved to read poems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.77,0:13:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She said that she used to\Nread poems with Mr. Schuwald
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when he could still see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.64,0:13:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.22,0:13:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look. I've kept these\Nin memory of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.39,0:14:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The poetry collections on this shelf
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.69,0:14:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,are all presents to my mother\Nfrom Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.90,0:14:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the detective in charge of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.33,0:14:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the "Dornach Company president\Nmurder case"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.04,0:14:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is now just a private detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.94,0:14:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You used to be\Nthe president's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask you once more\Nif anyone held a grudge against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.25,0:14:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,His enemies? There's not\Nenough time to count them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The police should have already\Ninvestigated the businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that went bankrupt\Nbecause of Mr. Gauk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.19,0:14:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another powerful\Nbusinessman in Bavaria, isn't there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What was Mr. Gauk's relationship\Nwith him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.17,0:14:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schuwald, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.70,0:14:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they were life-long rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.77,0:14:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.88,0:14:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald went bankrupt twice\Nin the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.38,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,His second bankruptcy was the result\Nof a fierce business war
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.22,0:15:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with Mr. Gauk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.55,0:15:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Mr. Gauk\Ncrushed Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.59,0:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There were times when Mr. Schuwald\Ndefeated the president as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.46,0:15:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They both hated each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.53,0:15:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.20,0:15:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It was terrible if they\Nhappened to meet at a party.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They had explosive fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.01,0:15:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, even though\Nthey're both cold-hearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But they were the only people\Nthey could talk to on the same level.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't really rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.32,0:15:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They were really more like friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.09,0:16:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I knew Hans well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.69,0:16:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He was one of the two people killed\Nin the "Voice of God murder case."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.90,0:16:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He was such a good man.\NHow unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.60,0:16:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Hans really such a good man?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He'd often treat me to a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He used to drive for Schwald, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently. But that was\Nthirty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.42,0:16:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why he was fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.89,0:16:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was around the time\Nthat Schuwald went bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.36,0:16:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They never had any problems\Nbetween them, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. I'm going to say this\Nin honor of Hans...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.60,0:17:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good-natured man\Nwho could get along with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.80,0:17:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even filthy rich bastards like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.07,0:17:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that "Vampire of Bavaria"'\Nor poor people like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.81,0:17:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He often said that he was the one\Nwho taught that tycoon how to bird-watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.78,0:17:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bird-watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.62,0:17:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Hans said that Schuwald\Nwas more like a happy child
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.95,0:17:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,than a vampire when\Nhe took him to the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.23,0:17:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already been two years since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.99,0:17:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, whenever I think\Nof my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was always\Na very serious man
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.57,0:17:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who never did anything\Nto be hated by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.04,0:17:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But...he was killed\Nin such a terrible way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.21,0:17:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for asking,\Nbut I believe your husband was an...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.61,0:17:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He lived in an orphanage\Nwhen he was younger,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and was shoved off\Nto various foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.22,0:17:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After a miserable childhood,\Nhe became an accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.99,0:17:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schuwald asked your husband\Nto be his corporate accountant,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.29,0:17:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.33,0:17:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.23,0:18:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But my husband always\Nturned him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.63,0:18:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only was he busy with\Nthe work he had at the time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,His philosophy towards money was\Nvery different from Mr. Schuwald's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.44,0:18:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was very honest\Nwhen it came to money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.68,0:18:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.21,0:18:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the culprit be caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.72,0:18:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll catch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.22,0:18:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,– Excuse me.\N– Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how your husband\Nand Mr. Schuwald met?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.33,0:18:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He said that they met\Nin the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.30,0:18:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It was when Mr. Schuwald\Ncould still see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They met in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.34,0:18:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What were they doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.81,0:18:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They were bird-watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.81,0:18:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They went together\Nmany times after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.32,0:19:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bird-watching.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.63,0:19:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like a happy child.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.23,0:19:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Read together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.07,0:19:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Friends.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.48,0:19:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.28,0:19:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm fine.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What horrible driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked more like he was\Ntrying to hit you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.63,0:19:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein, I've collected\Nall the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.36,0:19:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as I told you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.30,0:19:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The many cases that troubled me\Nwhen I was a police detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.34,0:19:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...all point in the same direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.64,0:19:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Voice of God murder case"!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.91,0:19:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Dornach Company president\Nmurder case"!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The "accountant murder case"!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.12,0:20:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They appear to have\Nnothing in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.39,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The methods in which they were\Ncommitted were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.86,0:20:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims didn't have any relation\Nto one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.36,0:20:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, they didn't have\Nany financial ties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.56,0:20:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is something\Nthat wasn't recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There is something\Nthat connects them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The deaths of all the victims\Nwere used to isolate Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.81,0:20:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There is also\Nanother strange connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the "Dornach Company president\Nmurder case",
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the man who Mr. Gauk\Nwas supposed to meet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.49,0:20:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,right before he was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.83,0:20:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the "Voice of God murder case",
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the god whose name\Nthe murderer scribbled on the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.87,0:20:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's the middle-aged couple\Nmultiple homicides.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The one case that seemed\Nto be unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.71,0:21:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the culprit named by\Nthe material witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.41,0:21:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.11,0:21:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They all had the same name!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.78,0:21:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.18,0:21:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My former student,\Na criminal psychologist,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was studying a murderer\Nwho committed his crimes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.19,0:21:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on a friend's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.09,0:21:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me in his letter.\NThat friend's name was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.07,0:21:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.70,0:21:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a common name. It's possible that\Nthe cases are related.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.18,0:21:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But if this is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.91,0:21:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he's been systematically murdering\Npeople for the past four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.02,0:21:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The man known as Johan
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.08,0:21:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to force Schuwald\Ninto complete isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.22,0:21:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer, the woman who bore\NSchuwald's son conveniently died.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.03,0:21:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the student who pretended\Nto be Schuwald's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.93,0:22:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He also conveniently killed himself\Nas soon as he made his claim.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.40,0:22:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If Johan really does exist,\Nwhere is he right now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.51,0:22:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So Johan's coming along.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.29,0:22:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Johan, the weather is beautiful.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.23,0:22:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes. Very.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.00,0:22:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right next to Schuwald!
